At the start of the study, their average cholesterol levels were 251. In the study, 421 people who recovered from heart attacks underwent the surgery, while a comparison group of 417 people were treated with diet alone. It has a role in the management of patients with high cholesterol who have had a heart attack, Buchwald said. This reduces the amount of cholesterol that is absorbed into the bloodstream. An intestinal operation to lower the cholesterol of heart attack patients reduced their risk for another heart attack or death from heart disease, researchers said today. 